    "title": "Privacy and Security",
    "content": "<div class='col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2'><h2>Privacy and Security</h2><h3><strong>Purpose of Privacy / Personal Data Protection Policy&nbsp;</strong></h3><p><strong>This Privacy / Personal Data Protection Policy;</strong></p><p>a. Invismile Estetik Dental Medikal San. ve Tic. Ltd. Şti.'s (Invismile Estetik Dental Medikal) online shopping platform&nbsp; <a href='https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.tamertanca.com.tr/&amp;sa=D&amp;ust=1563819930239000'>www.invismile.com.tr</a> &nbsp;(“invismile.com.tr”) collects personal data,</p><p>b. How this personal data is used,</p><p>c. With whom invismile.com.tr can share your personal data,</p><p>ç. What are your rights over your personal data processed by invismile.com.tr and how you can exercise these rights,</p><p>D. It explains how you can change your positive or negative preferences for receiving electronic commercial messages.</p><p><strong>Your Processed Personal Data, Purpose and Basis of Personal Data Processing</strong></p><p>Invismile Estetik Dental Medikal, in order to provide better service to its customers and the Law No.5651 on the Regulation of Publications on the Internet and Fight Against Crimes Committed Through These Publications and the related secondary legislation, Law No.6563 on the Regulation of Electronic Commerce and related secondary legislation, Turkish Penalty No.5237 Within the framework of the legal obligation arising from the relevant legislation, especially the Law on the Protection of Personal Data No. 6698; Your personal data (name, surname, date of birth, mobile phone number, e-mail, address, any personal information to identify the user directly or indirectly, including but not limited to the product information on the shop) demands from you.These personal data will be processed and stored in order to benefit from the benefits of membership of 'invismile.com.tr', based on your explicit consent, by taking information security measures, provided that they are not used outside the purposes and scope specified in this Privacy / Personal Data Protection Policy and Communication Permit.</p><p><strong>Communication Permission</strong></p><p>By accepting the 'Terms of Use' and this Privacy / Personal Data Protection Policy and Communication Permit, your personal information you have shared with us; In order to provide you with various advantages and to send all kinds of communication messages for sales, marketing and similar purposes; You expressly consent to its collection, storage, processing, use, transfer and sharing with Invismile Estetik Dental Medikal for the same purposes. This information is only for the purpose of providing the services to you perfectly, delivering your possible shipments in a healthy way, delivering our notifications via phone, sms and / or e-mail on time, we are in a contractual relationship, share our sensitivity about data security, comply with the provisions of the relevant legislation.will be shared with individuals only when needed and to the extent necessary.</p><p><strong>Your Rights Regarding Your Personal Data</strong></p><p>To learn what your processed personal data is, whether it is used for the purpose of processing, whether it is used for the purpose of processing, to learn about the third parties to whom personal data is transferred in the country or abroad, if there is incomplete or incorrectly processed personal data or if there is any change in your processed personal data, to change and update your personal data and / or You can access your account from the 'My Account' section on the 'invismile.com.tr' website and make necessary changes, updates and / or deletions in order to request that this situation be notified to third parties to whom your personal data has been transferred.</p><p><strong>Personal Data Retention Period</strong></p><p>Pursuant to the Law No. 6563 on the Regulation of Electronic Commerce; by recording the approval, withdrawal of approval, the content of the commercial electronic message and other records regarding the shipment to be submitted to the Ministry when necessary; it will be stored for 3 years from the date the approval expires. After the period has passed, your personal data are deleted, destroyed or anonymized by our company or upon your request. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Use of Cookies</strong></p><p>Cookies are text files that are loaded by your internet browser when you visit the 'invismile.com.tr' website and contain small pieces of information stored on your computer, mobile phone or tablet.</p><p>'Invismile.com.tr' will collect your browsing information in order to provide better service to its visitors, to benefit its visitors and members from the benefits of membership, and within the framework of its legal obligation, provided that it is not used outside of the purposes and scope specified by this Privacy / Personal Data Protection Policy and Communication Permit, will process it, share it with third parties and store it securely.</p><p>'Invismile.com.tr', for the purpose of promoting you, offering promotions and marketing offers, improving the content of the website for you and / or determining your preferences; tracks your browsing information on the site and / or your membership usage history on the site. 'Invismile.com.tr' uses session cookies and persistent cookies on its website and mobile site. Session ID cookie expires when you close your browser. The persistent cookie remains on your hard disk for a long time. You can remove persistent cookies and reject both session cookies and persistent cookies by following the instructions given in the 'help' file of your internet browser or by visiting 'www.allaboutcookies.org' or 'www.youronlinechoices.eu'. If you refuse persistent cookies or session cookies,You can continue to use the website and mobile site, but you may not be able to access all functions of the website and mobile site or your access may be limited.</p><p>How does 'invismile.com.tr' use third-party cookies for advertising and retargeting?</p><p>'Invismile.com.tr' cookies also; You can use search engines to activate 'Advertising Technology' in order to provide you with advertisements that you think may be of interest when you visit the 'invismile.com.tr' website or mobile site and / or websites where 'invismile.com.tr' advertises. Advertising Technology uses information about your previous visits to the website / mobile site and websites / mobile site where 'invismile.com.tr' advertises in order to offer you special advertisements. When serving these advertisements, a third party cookie may be placed on your browser so that 'invismile.com.tr' can recognize you. The website / mobile site of “invismile.com.tr” also; Google, Inc. ('Google') uses Google Analytics and Google Adwords, a web analysis service.Google Analytics and Google Adwords cookies are used to analyze how visitors use the website / mobile site. Information about your use of this website / mobile site (including your IP address) is transferred to Google and stored by Google. Google will use this information to evaluate your use of the website / mobile site, to compile the 'invismile.com.tr' website / mobile site activity and to provide other services related to website / mobile site activity and internet usage. However, it will not match your IP address with other data stored by Google. For more information on using Google Analytics, you can visit:Information about your use of this website / mobile site (including your IP address) is transferred to Google and stored by Google. Google will use this information to evaluate your use of the website / mobile site, to compile the 'invismile.com.tr' website / mobile site activity and to provide other services related to website / mobile site activity and internet usage. However, it will not match your IP address with other data stored by Google. For more information on using Google Analytics, you can visit:Information about your use of this website / mobile site (including your IP address) is transferred to Google and stored by Google. Google will use this information to evaluate your use of the website / mobile site, to compile the 'invismile.com.tr' website / mobile site activity and to provide other services related to website / mobile site activity and internet usage. However, it will not match your IP address with other data stored by Google. For more information on using Google Analytics, you can visit:tr ”will use it to compile the website / mobile site activity and to provide other services related to website / mobile site activity and internet usage. However, it will not match your IP address with other data stored by Google. For more information on using Google Analytics, you can visit:tr ”will use it to compile the website / mobile site activity and to provide other services related to website / mobile site activity and internet usage. However, it will not match your IP address with other data stored by Google. For more information on using Google Analytics, you can visit:&nbsp;<a href='https://www.google.com/url?q=http://www.google.com/intl/tr/policies/privacy/%23infocollect&amp;sa=D&amp;ust=1563819930243000'>http://www.google.com/intl/tr/policies/privacy/#infocollect</a> .</p><p><strong>Unsubscribe</strong></p><p>If you do not want to withdraw your consent and send the messages sent to you with the purpose of campaign promotions or information, you can send an e-mail to satis@invismile.com.tr at any time or click the exit link in the messages sent to you or contact Invismile Estetik Dental Medikal customer service. '……………….' You can report by calling number.</p><p><strong>Sharing Personal Data with Official Authorities</strong></p><p>Invismile Estetik Dental Medikal, your personal data related to membership and your traffic information such as your navigation information; for your safety and for Invismile Estetik Dental Medikal to fulfill its obligations under the law (in cases such as crime fighting, threat to the state and public security), it may share this information with the public institutions and organizations legally authorized to request this information.</p><p><strong>Precautions Regarding Protection of Personal Data</strong></p><p>Protection of personal data is an important issue for Invismile Estetik Dental Medikal. Invismile Estetik Dental Medikal takes necessary measures to protect personal data against unauthorized access or loss, misuse, disclosure, alteration or destruction of this information. Invismile Estetik Dental Medical uses generally accepted security technology standards such as firewalls and Secure Socket Layer (SSL) encryption when storing personal data. In addition, when sending your personal data to Invismile Estetik Dental Medikal through the website / mobile site, these data are transferred using SSL.</p><p>Invismile Estetik Dental Medikal undertakes to keep your personal data confidential, to take all necessary technical and administrative measures and to show the necessary care to ensure privacy and security. Although Invismile Estetik Dental Medikal takes the necessary information security measures, in the event that personal data is damaged or seized by third parties as a result of attacks on the website and the system, Invismile Estetik Dental Medikal immediately notifies you and the Personal Data Protection Board.</p><p><strong>Changes to Privacy / Personal Data Protection Policy and Communication Permit</strong></p><p>Invismile Estetik Dental Medikal can always make changes to this Privacy / Personal Data Protection Policy and Communication Permit. These changes become effective immediately upon the posting of the amended new Privacy / Personal Data Protection Policy and Communication Permit on the 'www.invismile.com.tr' site. Necessary information will be given to you, our members, in order to be aware of the changes in this Privacy / Personal Data Protection Policy and Communication Permit.</p><p><strong>Applicable Law, Authorized Courts and Enforcement Offices</strong></p><p>This Privacy / Data Protection Policy and Communication Permit is subject to the laws of the Republic of Turkey. Gaziantep Central Court and Enforcement Offices are authorized to resolve any disputes that may arise from the implementation of the Privacy / Personal Data Protection Policy and Communication Permit.</p></div>"
